        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 23 at 2:06AM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 205 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 6 miles north of Comanche to near Goldthwaite.
Movement was east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Proctor Lake and Comanche around 210 AM CDT.
Gustine around 225 AM CDT.

Other locations impacted by these storms include Shive, Moline,
Harbin, Bozar, Duster, Edna Hill, Comyn, Center City, Energy, and
Star.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 700 AM CDT for
central and north central Texas.</instruction>
